plan_generation.prompt:
Based on the public information:
{environment->public_information}
and your goal:
{agents->schedule_generator->goal}
Generate various possible schedules for the day. Remember to start at {environment->init->start_location} at {environment->init->start_time}.

verification.prompt:
Analyze the following proposed schedules:
{proposed_schedules}
Your private knowledge includes:
{agents->auditor->private_information}
Verify if these schedules satisfy all constraints, especially the 75-minute minimum meeting duration and William's availability.

pddl.prompt:
Based on the verification report:
{verified_schedule_report}
Select the optimal schedule that successfully satisfies the goal:
{agents->orchestrator->goal}
Translate this successful plan into a PDDL domain and problem. Ensure the PDDL clearly models time, locations (Nob Hill, The Castro), travel actions, and the meeting action, proving that the constraints (especially the 75-minute minimum duration) are met. Note the starting time is 9:00 AM.
